com.robindrew.common.collect.indexmap

Class ArrayIndexMap<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.robindrew.common.collect.indexmap.ArrayIndexMap<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - the indexed object type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IIndexMap<V>

    public class ArrayIndexMap<V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements IIndexMap<V>
    A thread safe map from an integer to an object, with extremely fast reads.

    Requires that the indexes are sequential and limited to relatively low integer values.

      • putAll

        public void putAll(java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,V> indexToValueMap)
        This method is optimised to put large numbers of entries in to the map.

        Although it does a double pass over the entries in the map, it is still orders of magnitude faster for large maps.
